<paragraph blockId="22.[159,762,569,1949]" pageId="22" pageNumber="414">Diagnosis — Dorsal shield colour pattern consisting of a light-reddish elongated central patch; lateral margins posterior to IV-L insertions with developed triangular projection on each side of ventral shield.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[159,762,569,1949]" pageId="22" pageNumber="414">
Description — Dorsal and ventral shields anteriorly lightly fused; dorsal shield with seven pairs of glandularia (the seventh pair inconspicuous, flanking the excretory pore); postocularia well distanced from anterior margin; excretory pore projecting, located at the posterior end of dorsal shield; anterior portion of dorsal shield with 14-15 pairs of triangular, posteriorly-directed (hyaline?) denticles (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="23.[159,171,1826,1845]" captionTargetBox="[250,1343,345,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-6@23.[242,1346,342,1794]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 13: Hexaxonopsis (Hexaxonopsis) laosensis n. sp., male, Kauangxi Waterfall, Laos: A – dorsal shield; B – ventral shield (arrow showing the projection on the lateral margin of the ventral shield); C-D – palp; E – gnathosoma; F – ejaculatory complex; G – I-L. Scale bars – 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5396020" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5396020/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="414">Figures 13A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[268,318,1328,1352]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="24.[159,171,1584,1603]" captionTargetBox="[252,1330,611,1543]" captionTargetId="figure-5@24.[242,1346,611,1552]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 14: Hexaxonopsis (Hexaxonopsis) laosensis n. sp., female, Kauangxi Waterfall, Laos: A – dorsal shield; B – ventral shield; C – palp. Scale bars – 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5396024" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5396024/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="414">14A</figureCitation>
); dorsal shield colour as shown in 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="25.[159,171,1663,1682]" captionTargetBox="[242,1345,532,1632]" captionTargetId="figure-6@25.[242,1345,532,1632]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 15: Photoghraphs of dorsal shield. A-B Hexaxonopsis laosensis n. sp.: A – male holotype; B – female paratype. C-D H. cambodiensis n. sp.: A – male holotype; B – female paratype. E – H. angkoriensis n. sp., female holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5396028" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5396028/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="414">Figures 15</figureCitation>
A-B; eye pigment well developed. Ventral shield oval, slightly truncate at anterior end, lateral margins rounded, with well developed triangular projection on each side (
<figureCitation box="[445,584,1469,1493]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="23.[159,171,1826,1845]" captionTargetBox="[250,1343,345,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-6@23.[242,1346,342,1794]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 13: Hexaxonopsis (Hexaxonopsis) laosensis n. sp., male, Kauangxi Waterfall, Laos: A – dorsal shield; B – ventral shield (arrow showing the projection on the lateral margin of the ventral shield); C-D – palp; E – gnathosoma; F – ejaculatory complex; G – I-L. Scale bars – 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5396020" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5396020/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="414">Figures 13B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[589,635,1469,1493]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="24.[159,171,1584,1603]" captionTargetBox="[252,1330,611,1543]" captionTargetId="figure-5@24.[242,1346,611,1552]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 14: Hexaxonopsis (Hexaxonopsis) laosensis n. sp., female, Kauangxi Waterfall, Laos: A – dorsal shield; B – ventral shield; C – palp. Scale bars – 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5396024" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5396024/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="414">14B</figureCitation>
), posterior to the insertions of IV-L. Lateral margins of Cx-I/II with 1-3 strong, hook-like, posteriorly-directed projections; two pairs of glandularia in region between genital field and opening for insertion of IV-L, these relatively close together; a relatively long longitudinal ridge posterior to IV-L insertions. Genital field with three pairs of Ac, arranged in an arc. Palp: ventral margin of P-2 convex, distal margin of P- 3 with well developed hyaline extensions, ventral margin of P-4 convexly protruding in the centre, here with two seta (one long and heavy, another long and slender) on small elevated ridges (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="23.[159,171,1826,1845]" captionTargetBox="[250,1343,345,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-6@23.[242,1346,342,1794]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 13: Hexaxonopsis (Hexaxonopsis) laosensis n. sp., male, Kauangxi Waterfall, Laos: A – dorsal shield; B – ventral shield (arrow showing the projection on the lateral margin of the ventral shield); C-D – palp; E – gnathosoma; F – ejaculatory complex; G – I-L. Scale bars – 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5396020" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5396020/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="414">Figures 13</figureCitation>
C-D,14C). Legs: number of swimming setae: II-
</paragraph>
